subprocess functions mix stdout with stderr (readme.ja)

Detect subprocess termination more robustly

Looking at the text of the event string provided to the process
sentinel is brittle.  We cannot really anticipate the many different
values this might have, and therefore cannot anticipate how to respond
to all of them.  For example, if the subprocess crashes due to a
SIGSEGV, then the event text might read "segmentation fault (core
dumped)".  The preexisting sentintel code did not check for this
specific string, and therefore would never realize that the subprocess
had terminated.

The new approach uses Emacs process management functions
like (process-live-p ...), (process-status ...),
and (process-exit-status ...).  These let us determine the process's
current status much more precisely, including more detailed
information about how/why it terminated.
